                        </textClass></profileDesc><revisionDesc><listChange><change><date>2016-10-31T13:39:19Z</date> | <name>Regina Roth</name> | <orgName>Telota</orgName> | OxGarage DOCX to TEI | 2.15.0</change><change><date>2016-10-31T14:57:10+01:00</date> | <name>Sascha Grabsch</name> | <orgName>Telota</orgName> | convert_tei_file.py | 0.85</change></listChange></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div type="writingSession"><opener><dateline><pb/> 4 Mai. 1866.</dateline><salute>My dear friend,</salute></opener><p>As I am at this moment, <seg type="comment"><orig>after so long an
                                                  interruption of work,</orig><note xml:id="b7611d02-0ceb-4d5a-9261-88f28269ccaf">Marx
                                                  war Anfang 1866 an Furunkulose erkrankt (siehe
                                                  <ref target="B00036">Marx an Engels,
                                                  10.2.1866</ref><?oxy_comment_start author="strauss" timestamp="20170718T185252+0200" comment="Br. 33 u. Erl 33a"?>
                                                  und Erl.)<?oxy_comment_end?>.</note></seg> very
                                        busily engaged in making up for lost time, you will excuse
                                        me for writing this time only a few lines.</p><p><anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="start_uts_wby_pz"/><anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="start_rpn_rzy_pz"/>I
                                        shall send you to-day the last number of the <bibl sameAs="ed_etf_mhf_lbb">“Commonwealth”.</bibl>
                                        <anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="stop_uts_wby_pz"/>The
                                        financial position of the paper is such that it struggles
                                        from week to week and is altogether disabled from paying one
                                        farthing for Foreign Correspondence. Its circulation is
                                        increasing, but you know that a penny paper wants at least
                                        20 000 subscribers, and cannot even then make the
                                        two ends meet without a goodly number of advertisements.
                                                <seg type="comment"><orig>The <bibl sameAs="ed_etf_mhf_lbb">“Commonwealth”</bibl> is of too recent an origin
                                                  to come up to those requisites.</orig><anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="stop_rpn_rzy_pz"/><note xml:id="c0dd2747-79c8-491e-9fe0-343e7ee34208">Zur
                                                  Zeitung <bibl sameAs="ed_etf_mhf_lbb">„The Commonwealth“</bibl> siehe
                                                  Erl. zu <ref target="B00007/#nmrb_qzn_4y">Marx an
                                                  J. Ph. Becker, zw. 9. u.
                                                  15.1.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T121136+0200" comment="{{Erl. 6f}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.
                                                  <!--(((zThe_Commonwealth)))-->
                                                </note></seg></p><p><seg type="comment"><orig>The Congress at Geneva has been postponed for
                                                  the 3<hi rendition="#sup">d</hi> of September
                                                  next.</orig><note xml:id="f04af7ee-c5b0-42c5-bc50-dda86bd2e192">Der
                                                  Beschluss über die Verlegung des Genfer Kongresses
                                                  der IAA (siehe <ref target="B00004/#nrk1_sfc_3y">Erl. zu Marx an Engels,
                                                  5.1.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T121514+0200" comment="{{Erl. 3d}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>)
                                                  auf den 3. September 1866 wurde in der
                                                  Sitzung des Zentralrats der IAA am 1. Mai
                                                  1866 angenommen (siehe <bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-7U8R32JW">The Minute Book 1864–1866.</bibl> In:
                                                  MEGA² I/20. S. 405/406 und MEGA² I/20.
                                                  Erl. 403.14-15).
                                                  <!--(((lThe Minute Book
                                                  1864–1866. In: MEGA² I/20. S. 265–450)))-->
                                                </note></seg>
                                        <seg type="comment"><orig>The society</orig><note xml:id="aaaf981f-b722-4313-8f29-3b2f4f2a44ce">Die
                                                  IAA.</note></seg> is rapidly <expan>sp<supplied cert="high">rea</supplied>ding</expan>, particularly in
                                        France. <seg type="comment"><orig>Italian societies
                                                  ha<supplied cert="high">ve</supplied> also
                                                  recently joined.</orig><note xml:id="f7b2a3f9-2fdd-41a9-82f6-155044fe4360">Siehe <ref target="B00102/#start_wgf_ytx_pz">H.
                                                  Jung an Marx,
                                                  2.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170419T140330+0200" comment="{{Br. 98.4–19}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.</note></seg>
                                        <seg type="comment"><orig>The propaganda in London has <del rendition="#s">been</del><sic ana="#break-off"/>
                                                  taken a new start, principally due to the <subst>
                                                  <del rendition="#s">circumstances</del>
                                                  <add place="intralinear">circumstance</add>
                                                  </subst> that the successful strikes of the London
                                                  tailors and wireworkers were due to our
                                                  intervention which prevented the <pb/> import of
                                                  workingmen from France, Switzerland, Belgium,
                                                  which had been contemplated by the masters. This
                                                  proof <subst>
                                                  <del>the</del>
                                                  <add>its</add>
                                                  </subst> immediate <subst>
                                                  <del>practically</del>
                                                  <add>practical</add>
                                                  </subst>
                                                  <expan>import<ex>ance</ex></expan> has struck the
                                                  practical English mind.</orig><note xml:id="c451667f-9ff3-4d12-9f03-45fe0b1ad055">Zum
                                                  Streik der Schneider in Großbritannien und der
                                                  Unterstützung durch die IAA siehe <ref target="B00097/#aaa785b0-040b-4650-8a8f-dad401bdbf2e">Erl. zu Marx an Engels,
                                                  23.4.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T121753+0200" comment="{{Erl. 93b}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>
                                                  und <ref target="B00100/#f2403266-7696-4a99-9654-89d0dd7a2f83">Erl. zu Engels an Marx,
                                                  1.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T121936+0200" comment="{{96c}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?>.</ref></note></seg></p><p><seg type="comment"><orig><anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="start_mdv_srw_pz"/><anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="start_nsm_4cx_pz"/>For
                                                  the same purpose you find, on the last page of
                                                  this letter an “avis” to the German tailors which
                                                  I call upon you to have inserted in such German
                                                  papers as you have access to.</orig><note xml:id="a0a9d14b-c89c-41d8-a8cd-54915be9b3b7"><bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-EEF5T5QH">Karl Marx: Warnung.</bibl> In:
                                                  MEGA² I/20. S. 204/205). Siehe auch <ref target="B00100/#f2403266-7696-4a99-9654-89d0dd7a2f83">Erl. zu Engels an Marx,
                                                  1.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T122711+0200" comment="{{Erl. 96c}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>
                                                  und <ref target="B00104/#bd09c828-996e-4e56-977c-a9f2777c8c76">Erl. zu A. F. Haufe und F. Leßner an Marx,
                                                  3.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T123008+0200" comment="{{100b}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.
                                                  Zur Veröffentlichung des Aufrufs siehe <ref target="B00107">W. Liebknecht an Marx, zw. 8. u.
                                                  15.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170419T140549+0200" comment="{{Br. 103.18-24}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>
                                                  und <ref target="B00107/#nowq_vcx_dz">Erl. zu W.
                                                  Liebknecht an Marx,
                                                  15.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170509T123403+0200" comment="{{Erl. 103j}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.</note></seg>
                                        At the same time you will oblige me by sending me a copy, or
                                        two, of <subst>
                                                <del>those</del>
                                                <add>some</add>
                                        </subst> papers in which the “avis” will have been inserted,
                                        telling me at the same time the names of all
                                                <add>other</add> papers that should have reprinted
                                        it. <anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="stop_mdv_srw_pz"/><persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002616">Kugelmann</persName> might also be useful for this
                                                purpose.<anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="stop_nsm_4cx_pz"/></p><p>My best compliments to Mrs. <persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002819">Liebknecht</persName>. I feel exceedingly thankful for <subst><del>the</del><add>her</add></subst> friendly interest in my welfare.</p><closer>Yours fraternally<lb/>A. Williams. </closer></div></body></text></TEI>